OL,3,C'It is crystal clear that he is
OL,4,Cunfit': Lockerbie man avoids murder
OL,5,Ctrial
OL,7,FA court hearing at the High Court in
OL,8,FGlasgow was told that Hodge suffers
OL,9,Ffrom signs of dementia on Monday 10
OL,10,FFebruary 2025, following a cognitive
OL,11,Ftest on Hodge at a care home in July
OL,12,F2024.
OL,14,FCourt papers state Hodge caused her an
OL,15,Finjury by "means unknown to the
OL,16,Fprosecutor".
OL,18,FHodge also faces a separate charge of
OL,19,Fattempting to defeat the ends of
OL,20,Fjustice by disposing of Marion's body
OL,21,Fand personal effects.
