OL,3,C'It is crystal clear that he is
OL,4,Cunfit': Lockerbie man avoids murder
OL,5,Ctrial
OL,7,FProfessor Gary McPherson, the
OL,8,Fconsultant forensic clinical
OL,9,Fpsychologist who carried out the
OL,10,Ftesting, told the court: "He
OL,11,Fdemonstrates a number of deficits in
OL,12,Fattention, and he is unable to follow
OL,13,Fwhat is happening around him.
OL,15,F"He has deficits in memory, and he
OL,16,Fwasn't able to remember things after a
OL,17,Fshort time.
OL,19,F"He also has deficits in verbal
OL,20,Ffluency ` expressing two or three
OL,21,Fwords after a long pause."
